anything,
which
he
condescended
to
ask.
I
now
give
it
to
you,
if
you
are
resolved
on
having
him.
But
let
me
advise
you
to
think
better
of
it.
I
know
your
disposition,
Lizzy.
I
know
that
you
could
be
neither
happy
nor
respectable,
unless
you
truly
esteemed
your
husband;
unless
you
looked
up
to
him
as
a
superior.
Your
lively
talents
would
place
you
in
the
greatest
danger
in
an
unequal
