with
astonishment.
"This
is
an
evening
of
wonders,
indeed!
And
so,
Darcy
did
every
thing;
made
up
the
match,
gave
the
money,
paid
the
fellow's
debts,
and
got
him
his
commission!
So
much
the
better.
It
will
save
me
a
world
of
trouble
and
economy.
Had
it
been
your
uncle's
doing,
I
must
and
would
have
paid
him;
but
these
violent
young
lovers
carry
every
thing
their
own
way.
I
shall
offer
to
pay
him
to
morrow;
he
will
rant
and
storm
about
his
love
for
you,
and
there
will
be
an
end
